In a statement released by the White House, President Obama commemorates the 60th anniversary of the Brown v. Board of Education ruling. He emphasizes the significance of this landmark decision in dismantling the "separate but equal" doctrine that supported racial segregation. The President calls for a renewed commitment to fighting bigotry and racism in all forms, and affirms the belief that every child deserves an education that recognizes their potential. He acknowledges that achieving civil rights for all required years of struggle and a nationwide movement. The President also highlights the bravery of those who took risks to make the country more fair and free, and urges citizens to continue their legacy by working towards a more perfect union.